      • exec

        public java.lang.String exec(TerminalScanner scan,
                             DataModel model,

                      throws PermissionException,
                             CancelException,
                             java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                             java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Executing this scenario results in the possible selecting of a patch for a certain bug report.

        1. The developer indicates that he wants to select a patch for some bug report.
        2. Include use case Select Bug Report if required.
        3. The system shows a list of possible patches.
        4. The developer selects a patch.
        5. The system selects the patch for the bug report.
        Extensions: 5a. The developer does not have sufficient permissions.
        1. The use case ends here.

        Specified by:
        exec in interface Cmd<java.lang.String>
        Parameters:
        scan - The scanner used to interact with the person.
        model - The model used for model access.
        user - The User who wants to executes this command.
        Returns:
        The BugReport that a patch was selected for.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - When there are on patches.
        PermissionException - When the user does not have sufficient permissions.
        CancelException - When the users wants to abort the current cmd
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When scan or model or user == null
        See Also:
        DataModel.selectPatch(BugReport, User, String)
